# LLM Usage Rules

> **Important:** Cloud LLMs are **NOT integrated** in the core pipeline today (Whisper and sentence-transformers run locally).  
> **Token economics:** Read `docs/TOKEN_ECONOMICS.md` and `token_economics.mdc` before any LLM work.

## Cursor vs your APIs

- **Cursor:** write code, tests, provider abstraction — not bulk channel analysis in chat.
- **Your API keys:** run scripts that classify/synthesize at scale.

## Model routing (when implemented)

| Role | Provider |
|------|----------|
| Bulk classification, tagging, clustering | **DeepSeek** (or local) |
| Final synthesis (bibles, personas) | **Claude** — compressed JSON in only |
| Prompt engineering, plans, taxonomies | **GPT** |
| Trend / competitor research | **Grok** — sparingly |

## Pipeline pattern

```
Raw reports → DeepSeek extraction → structured JSON → Claude synthesis → cache
```

Never send raw video frames to LLMs. Preprocess first.

Store all LLM outputs as versioned artifacts under `artifacts/llm_cache/`.

Cache all expensive generations. Estimate tokens + cost before each call.

Config: `config.yaml` → `llm:` block. Code: `channel_analyzer/llm/` (**PLANNED**).
